
1. Why CSS? Inline vs. Internal vs. External 

  index.html 
<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html lang="en"> 
<head> 
  <meta charset="UTF-8"> 
  <title>Local Community Event Portal</title> 
 
  <!-- Internal (embedded) style --> 
  <style> 
    body { 
      background-color: #f4f4f4; 
    } 
  </style> 
 
  <!-- External stylesheet --> 
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css"> 
</head> 
<body> 
 
  <!-- Inline style --> 
  <h1 style="color: red;">Welcome to the Community Event Portal</h1> 
 
  <h2>Upcoming Events</h2> 
 
</body> 
</html> 
styles.css 
/* Header styles */ 
h1 { 
  font-size: 32px; 
} 
 
/* Body/reset styles */ 
body { 
  margin: 0; 
  padding: 0; 
} 
This shows all three CSS methods: inline (on the h1), internal (the <style> block in the head 
for the background), and external (the linked styles.css file, which is where reusable styles 
should generally live). 

  
  2. CSS Syntax and Comments 
styles.css (continued) 
/* ============================ 
Base Reset 
============================ */ 
* { 
margin: 0; 
padding: 0; 
box-sizing: border-box; 
} 
/* ============================ 
Navigation Styles 
============================ */ 
nav { 
background-color: #333; 
padding: 10px 20px; 
} 
/* ============================ 
Call To Action Button 
============================ */ 
/* Style for main CTA button */ 
.cta-button { 
background-color: #007BFF; 
color: white; 
padding: 10px 20px; 
border: none; 
border-radius: 4px; 
cursor: pointer; 
} 
.cta-button:hover { 
background-color: #0056b3; 
} 
Good CSS hygiene here: consistent 2-space indentation, one rule per line, and comment 
banners that section off the file so anyone joining the project can scan it quickly. 

  
  3. Selectors Playground 
/* Universal selector - reset margin/padding */ 
* { 
margin: 0; 
padding: 0; 
} 
/* Element selector - all h2 headings */ 
h2 { 
color: #2c3e50; 
font-size: 24px; 
} 
/* ID selector - the main banner */ 
#mainHeader { 
background-color: #007BFF; 
color: white; 
padding: 20px; 
text-align: center; 
} 
/* Class selector - event containers */ 
.eventCard { 
background-color: #fff; 
border: 1px solid #ddd; 
border-radius: 6px; 
padding: 15px; 
margin-bottom: 15px; 
} 
/* Grouping selector */ 
h3, p { 
font-family: Arial, sans-serif; 
line-height: 1.5; 
} 
