11. Debug and Test with Dev Tools and VS Code 
This one is a workflow exercise rather than code, so here's what to actually do: 
Open Chrome DevTools with F12 or Ctrl+Shift+I (Cmd+Option+I on Mac). 
Click the device toolbar icon (or Ctrl+Shift+M) to simulate phones, tablets, and desktops, and 
test the breakpoint from Exercise 10 by resizing. 
Use the Elements panel to click on any component (like .eventCard) and see its live CSS 
rules in the Styles pane; you can toggle properties on/off or edit values directly and watch the 
page update in real time. 
Open the Network tab, reload the page, and confirm styles.css shows a 200 status, so you 
know the external stylesheet actually loaded rather than silently failing. 
In VS Code, install the Live Server extension so you can right-click index.html and choose 
"Open with Live Server" — this auto-refreshes the browser every time you save a CSS change, 
which speeds up this whole debugging loop. 
